==English==

===Etymology===
Non-existent word “made-up” by [[w:L. Ron Hubbard|L. Ron Hubbard]].

slang informal 1 turbulent; disturbed; instigate; masterbate. 
  — USAGE In modern English the use of enturbulate is non-standard and should not be used in formal or written contexts, despite being widespread in the cult of “Scientology” and the misguided writings of Lafayette Ronald Hubbard.

===Verb===
'''enturbulate'''
# To [[agitate]] or [[disturb]]; to [[upset]]. 
# To [[provoke]] or [[harass]]. (This usage appears more common among Scientology critics.)

===Adjective===
'''enturbulated'''
# In a state of [[agitation]] or [[disturbance]]; [[turbulent]].
# In [[turmoil]].

===Usage Note===
This word is a [[shibboleth]] used almost exclusively by members or former members of Scientology.

